        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the filling",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cook the chopped onions gently in olive oil over low heat for 20 to 25 minutes until soft, golden, and sweet. Do not rush with high heat; the onions need to caramelise, not soften and steam. Season with salt, allow to cool completely, then stir in the poppy seeds. Set aside.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make and prove the dough",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Combine flour, yeast, and salt. Add the water and mix to a rough dough, then knead for 8 to 10 minutes until smooth and elastic. Cover and leave at room temperature for 1 hour until doubled.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Divide and shape",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Divide the dough into 8 pieces (about 80 g each). Shape each into a ball, then flatten into a disc about 10 cm across. Place on a lined baking tray, cover, and prove for 30 minutes. Preheat the oven to 230°C conventional.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Fill and bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Before baking, press a deep indent in the centre of each disc with your fingers and thumbs, pushing the dough outward to form a thin well. Spoon a teaspoon of the onion mixture into each well and spread it to cover the indent. Bake for 16 to 20 minutes until the edges are pale gold and the onion topping is lightly browned. Serve within a few hours of baking.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
